Issue : Avios redemption for Iberia partner Vinoseleccion was failing. Impact : Customers will not be able to redeem points, the partner sales will also be impacted. This will create bad image for Iberia, impact user experience and revenue loss. Analysis : We checked and saw that the contract between Iberia and Vinoselecion expired on 28th feb. Resolution : We checked with the concerned team and it was confirmed that the contract was over on 28th Feb and not before that.Also 707 is a generic error which might have been caused due to temporal blockage. On the days before 28th Feb when error code 707 was returned other errors were also returned as per logic which indicates that contract was not terminated before time. Can this issue be prevented : No, this was due to contract expiry Problem ticket required : No, this was due to contract expiry
Procedemos al reinicio de la contraseña del usuario tras seguir el proceso de seguridad.

incident description: ICC005: Some of the records not updated correctly in MDM in last run.
resolution description: ISSUE: ICC005: ICC005: Some of the records not updated correctly in MDM in last run, as re-processing of records were in process. ANALYSIS: We have identified that some of the records not updated correctly in MDM in last run, as re-processing of records were in process. Also observed that for 2nd & 3rd march, we have recived hug data from upstream system which impacted the MDM batch performance. BUSINESS IMPACT: Due to this issue there will be delay in customer data update to downsteam system. RESOLTUION: This is not an issue. We have retriggered the batch with small chunk of data and executed successfully. PROBLEM TICKET REQUIRED?: No, This is an intermittent issue. We can not reproduce it. CAN THIS ISSUE BE PREVENTED?: No, This is an intermittent issue. We can not reproduce it.

Issue:AIP has reported that they have not received golden id information in Marketing file for those received in Customer file . Analysis: We have received an incident where you had reported that a series of golden_id record is not coming in the MDM marketing files but present in Customer file . We have checked these records in Customer file and sent to source team for further analysis . Impact:If information is not correct in mdm files it will impact the information ingested by downclients which fetch data from AIP. Resolution: We havechecked with MDM team to know the logic behind this if the records are being filtered out or the reason for unavailability of these golden id records in Marketing file . MDM team has reviewed the golden records and observed all records are created via RESTKT source. Any record that flown thru RESTKT input file doesn’t have marketing permission in it. Since MDM haven’t receive marketing permissions for those records, therefore it populate NULL in MKT_PERMISSION table in MDM system . As per logic, marketing permission only flows via IBCOM and IBPLUS source . Problem Ticket:No- This issue does not happen frequently . Preventive Action: No -This is data issue hence can not be prevented .
Procedemos al reinicio de la contraseña del usuario tras seguir el proceso de seguridad.

incident description: ZFII158 : few reversal documents wre not sent to CFS in the past.
resolution description: Users complained that few invoices were not sent to CFS . Upon analysis the reversal documents 1700008639 and 1700008641 has a document status as A in the table BKPF in SAP. There is a program ZFII158 in SAP which collects all the documents to be sent to CFS. This job will not pick the documents whose status are A, Z or V as per the program logic.Like said earlier in the mail, both these documents were having Document status as 'A' hence these documents will not be sent to CFS. Explained the same to the user via mail with screenshots. Closing incident

Issue: Consulta sobre subvenciones en E75 IMpact: Bajo Root Causes: Por lo que se ha podido comprobar esta casuística se está dando para aquellos cupones facturados por CRS, ya que no se obtiene su valor de la rutina de subvención del R50, sino que los importes de subvención se obtienen directamente de las tablas de CRS (TIPGCBC). En estos cupones su valor en dicha tabla es cero. Analizando más a fondo este asunto, el importe de subvención que se carga a su vez en CRS’s proviene del aplicativo A39, en concreto la tabla TCVECSB, y no hay información en ella para estos cupones, por ello se quedan con importe 0. El origen de estos casos en concreto es ATPCO, y en el flujo de este origen para los casos de compañías no está el aplicativo A39, con lo que no se insertan en la tabla en cuestión. Por tanto, estos cupones sólo tomarán importe de subvención si han llegado también desde otro origen que sí pase por el A39. Si se requiriera que este conjunto se incluyera en el A39 serían necesarios nuevos procesos y por tanto un desarrollo, incluimos a Julio en este sentido. STeps taken: Se notifica a cliente.

incident description: [ICC002] SALESFORCE SERVICE CLOUD FF-97094239/ P20210302-12607847 Presidencia
resolution description: Issue: I wanted to open an incident because the customer iberia plus 97094239, does not appear in sales force correctly, when searching for it by FF in sales force appears another customer, please, is it possible to investigate it? Analysis: Analyzed the issue and found that data was correct for the customer iberia plus 97094239. Business Impact: There could have be data discrepancies if the data was not consistence throughout the systems. Resolution: Below steps followed to check: 1. Checked in Atos system, Customer data is correct. 2. Checked in MDM, Customer data is correct. 3. Checked in Salesforce, Customer data is correct. According to existing design Primary Frequent Flyer number should be use to search and refer to the details of customer, which in this case is IB11978970(Golden Id# 212838162). If anyone searches on salesforce with any secondary Frequent Flyer number (i.e IB97094239), we get the details of “Programa de Fidelizacion”. If we directly search with 97094239 (without IB) it will give you two results in salesforce one for “Clientes” and another for “Programa de Fidelizacion”. The first search is not valid because it is taking id golden record “97094239” and displaying it in search result (if you search with IB97094239 this customer will not appear). CAN THIS ISSUE BE PREVENTED?: No. data was consistent in Atos, MDM and Salesforce. PROBLEM TICKET REQUIRED?: No. data was consistent in Atos, MDM and Salesforce.

incident description: CLAIMS AUTO I DOES TO EXECUTE ALL EXPEDIENTES
resolution description: issue - Due to claims Automation some cases were not moved to other queues if they are not processed automatically. impact - if queue is not moved, then the case will stay the same and will not be actioned which will lead to late resolution of cases. incident description: Severity 2, Amadeus Selling Platform Connect - Login: IR 20894827
resolution description: Issue Description :Severity 2, Amadeus Selling Platform Connect - Login: IR 20894827. Business Impact -: Some customers in certain locations were not able to open SECO (Amadeus Selling Platform Connect - www.sellingplatformconnect.amadeus.com). Analysis : Amadeus has been informed by Imperva that they are currently experiencing a Domain Name Server(DNS) issue which is impacting accessibility to Amadeus Selling Platform Connect application in some markets. Imperva are an external third party company who provide web application security. Customer Impact Customers in some markets may be experiencing sign-in related errors on Amadeus Selling Platform Connect and thus, may be prevented from signing-in into the application. Work-around information No workaround has been identified however support teams are continuing to assess. Action taken: Followed up to Amadeus for the ongoing issue. Problem Ticket : n/a , IR 20895710 was raised for follow up. Prevent Measures :IR 20895710 was raised for follow up.

incident description: KO in OBHCIP OBHCIP: KO proceso FISION FICHERO PARTIAL_REVERSAL_*_IBC.trn
resolution description: Issue: KO in OBHCIP OBHCIP: KO proceso FISION FICHERO PARTIAL_REVERSAL_*_IBC.trn Analysis: Analyzed the issue and found that we have not received the files in the below location that's why load plan got failed. files directory: /obhcip/input/comarch Business Impact: Delay in file execution will impact Iberia cards since it holds Reversal points data, consumed by partners of the loyalty program and hence the users will not be able to see the updated Reversal points against their Iberia Cards. Resolution: Re ran the ODI Load plan for Partial Reversal file to successfully process the file. PKG_FISION_FICHEROS_PARTIAL_REVERSAL_trn_out CAN THIS ISSUE BE PREVENTED?: No. The File was delayed from the source Team and therefore, no issue with the application. PROBLEM TICKET REQUIRED?: No. As the files are received from the source Team. There was delay in sending the files due to which the load Plan failed.
Se informa al usuario del proceso de seguridad.
Procedemos al reinicio de la contraseña del usuario tras seguir el proceso de seguridad.

Issue: Iberia cards required ENROLMENTR files sequence from 00001253 - 00001255. Analysis: Analyzed the issue and found that these sequence are already sent from Iberia side but Iberia cards team has not received. Need to retransmit the files. Business Impact: Delay in file execution will impact Iberia cards since it holds Reversal points data, consumed by partners of the loyalty program and hence the users will not be able to see the updated Reversal points against their Iberia Cards. Resolution: Retransmitted the below sequences using below load plan: Sequence Sent: 00001253 - 00001255 Load Plan: PKG_OFFLINE_ENROLMENT_out CAN THIS ISSUE BE PREVENTED?: No. This is not a recurring issue. PROBLEM TICKET REQUIRED?: No. As Iberia card team just need these files again.

[Issue]:Booking is retrieved to generate the template but the product returned by Optima is "EXPRESS", not "PRIORITISE".. [Impact]:User will not able to create template booking on iagcargo.com [Analysis]: If user makes a PRIORITISE booking on iagcargo.com and later if they changes the Booking product type using  (Optima or BA80 ) after when user creates on iagcargo.com a new template out of that booking then that template has Express and not PRIORITISE as product type and system will throw the below error ("booking product not valid")   [Step Taken to Resolve]: Sent an email to user as below Subject updated with the correct incident number.   Thanks for the sharing the attached XMLs in the previous email.   As per our discussion over the teams call yesterday and below are the problem statement in order to proceed with this issue.   Current behavior : If user makes a PRIORITISE booking on iagcargo.com and later if they changes the Booking product type using  (Optima or BA80 ) after when user creates on iagcargo.com a new template out of that booking then that template has Express and not PRIORITISE as product type and system will throw the below error ("booking product not valid") when user submit the booking.     Expected behavior: If user makes a booking <Prioritise, Perform Loose, Perform Unitised, Fresh, Secure> on iagcargo.com and user changes the booking product using ( Optima or BA80 ) after when user creates on iagcargo.com a new template out of that booking then that template will have <Prioritise, Perform Loose, Perform Unitised, Fresh, Secure> as product and it will allow me to submit the bookings without throwing any error.   We have just checked in the code and found out how the functionality for the booking product type is working and why the system is throwing an error in the template case.   As per the code we have been using this table “iag_products” and this table store the mapping for all the Booking product Type and we have checked in the table and could see that “Express” booking type was not present hence system is throwing an error against this issue.   We have extracted the table data for you to check and let us know if changes are required in order to fixed this permanently , Meantime we are checking the impact of this table in the other application.   We have closed this incident and have raised the problem ticket (PBI000000087055) to cover same for future work.   Please check the attached excel file and let us know what changes are required and accordingly we shall update the table in the non-live system and then we will book the non-environment for you to test the functionality. [Problem Ticket Required? (Yes, No).]:No [Can this incident be prevented? (Yes, No)]:No

Issue: Login failure in GaudiPr1 and that if during the afternoon it is not resolved it would be very urgent. Analysis: We have analyzed the issue and found that user is not able to login to GaudiPr1 platform because server is not accessible/ Services was hanged. Business Impact: Business were not able to access the reports, This caused delay in staff duties. Resolution: Below Steps were performed to resolve the issue: 1. Restarted the GaudiPr1 platform services but Hyperion S9 BI+ 9.2 Workspace service got stuck while stopping it. 2. Contact to csoporte team indicating them notify Windows ES and restart the services in GaudiPr1. 3. Service restarted by Windows ES team but still facing the same issue. 4. Checked the logs and found that tomcat is not able to connect to database due to database server is not available. 5. Connected with database team and found that there was one change due to file system got disconnected that’s why not able to connect to database. 6. Database team has restarted the server and after that services are started and running fine now. CAN THIS ISSUE BE PREVENTED?: No. this is not a recurring issue. PROBLEM TICKET REQUIRED?: No. as the issue is temporary.

Issue: Login failure in GaudiPr1 and that if during the afternoon it is not resolved it would be very urgent. Analysis: We have analyzed the issue and found that user is not able to login to GaudiPr1 platform because server is not accessible/ Services was hanged. Business Impact: Business were not able to access the reports, This caused delay in staff duties. Resolution: Below Steps were performed to resolve the issue: 1. Restarted the GaudiPr1 platform services but Hyperion S9 BI+ 9.2 Workspace service got stuck while stopping it. 2. Contact to csoporte team indicating them notify Windows ES and restart the services in GaudiPr1. 3. Service restarted by Windows ES team but still facing the same issue. 4. Checked the logs and found that tomcat is not able to connect to database due to database server is not available. 5. Connected with database team and found that there was one change due to file system got disconnected that’s why not able to connect to database. 6. Database team has restarted the server and after that services are started and running fine now. CAN THIS ISSUE BE PREVENTED?: No. this is not a recurring issue. PROBLEM TICKET REQUIRED?: No. as the issue is temporary.

Issue: issue ALERTA-CRI-GRUPOS-procapl1:CargaPra_210308-Error ALERTA-CRI_GRUPOSX_sercoml1:Carga_PNRs_Ext_ERROR Business Impact : Gru's process was unable to process the PNRs, it cause revenue impact Analysis : In the above mentioned error, we found that carga_pra fails becuase external pnr process not executed and generate the file /procusers/grupos/ficheros/pnr_ext/ r_ext210308053001 sucessfully, this file used by carga_pra process. Because of above mentioned external pnrs- TT value is 0, hence external process was unable to generat the file. /procusers/grupos/ficheros/pnr_ext/ r_ext210308053001 Step-3 Contact with Mantenimiento COBOL MantenimientoCOBOL@iberia.es and DS/SP/PASAJERES spres@iberia.es team. Step-4 If they will confirm that pnrs has been queued in the queue and we can check the same in scort tool and relaunch the process again. Step-5 If they confirm there was no pnrs in nightly process for TTQLM017 queue than we will create a file /procusers/grupos/ficheros/pnr_ext/ r_ext210308053001 manually by changing the date with at least one canceled pnr as mention below. Resolution : Than we will not relaunch the external pnrs process becuase external pnrs are not avilable at source. Just relaunch the carga_pnr process only, we can find the details of canceled pnrs from previous day’s file. Is Problem ticket req. : No, As per design the System is working fine. Preventive action requires : No, As per design the System is working fine.

resolution description: Issue Description: [COM] BKG | Reservas que se emiten correctamente pero no llegan a la página de confirmación Business Impact: there is an impact in google analytics tracing Analysis: we have investigated the issue but did not found any relevant error or exception that may have caused the error. resolution description: Issue Description :ALERTA-CRI:Iberia.com portal Splunk Alert: Alerta errores emision online Business Impact -: No, there is no overall degradation in payments on platform. Analysis : We can see a decrease in transactions for old web platform for which there is alreay an ongoing incident "INC000001498517 - Degradation detected at Amadeus payment gateway since 3/03/2021 15:00" It seems that certain traffic has been moved to NetPlus from Amadeus because from the same moment of time there is an upgradation in NetPlus Payments. And, there is no overall degradation in payments on platform. Action taken: We are proceeding to close this incident as we already have a an ongoing incident to check for the cause. Problem Ticket Required (y/n) : Not required, as this is a proactive check. Prevent Measures : Not required, as we have alert configured for same.

PROBLEM TICKET REQUIRED?: No. As the files are received from the source Team. There was delay in sending the files due to which the load Plan failed.

incident description: Cupones en tabla TBDPTID con info de mercados a cero
resolution description: Issue: Consulta sobre campos en TID Impact: Medio Root Causes: Se ha revisado la incidencia del asunto. Para estos casos hemos detectado varias casuísticas para el campo TID_CODMER: Cupones de compañías con utilización real, siempre van sin el campo mercado (7439769347, 2128243121, etc.). EMD's placa IB, dónde la venta llega con origen/destino ZZZ/ZZZ. En esos casos en las tablas de ventas no se recupera el mercado, y cuando existe la venta es de dónde se recupera para cargar el campo en la tabla TID de ingresos (1858297895, 1860233658). Cupones placa IB sin venta. En estos casos el mercado se recupera de la parte de utilización, y vemos que según los procesos cuando el cupón en la VOL tiene el campo VOLICR distinto de C, P u O el punto a punto se informa con asteriscos, luego que luego a su vez en los procesos de carga de utilización de la NBDP, hace que el mercado se calcule a 0's (9434473040). Si no encuentra en la VOL, parece que ocurriría lo mismo, pero no hemos visto ningún caso. Respecto a los campos TID_TIPPASAJ y TID_TIPTAR, sólo se informan cuando hay venta, es normal que haya casos que estén sin informar, siempre que sólo haya llegado la utilización. Steps taken: Se informa a cliente.

resolution description: Issue Description :ALERTA-CRI:Iberia.com portal Splunk Alert: Alerta errores emision online Business Impact -: No, there is no overall degradation in payments on platform. And, there is no overall degradation in payments on platform. Action taken: We are proceeding to close this incident as we already have a an ongoing incident to check for the cause. [CKI] Se revisa la incidencia y comprobamos que no hay ningún problema por parte del sistema. La situación fué la siguiente: - El pasajero se factura en ORY pero se queda en stby, por lo tanto el MADSCQ no lo factura. - Estando en stby, le meten y borran el HBCI, por lo que el HBCI cancelado en el MADSCQ es correcto. -una vez llega a puerta de embarque en ORY, al estar en stby, le hacen una AC y lo aceptan y embarcan, pero no facturan la continuación, solo el ORYMAD. Entonces, debido a esta casuistica, cuando el pasajero llega para hacer el MADSCQ, se encuentran que no está facturado.
Procedemos al reinicio de la contraseña del usuario tras seguir el proceso de seguridad.

resolution description: Issue Description :ALERTA-CRI:Iberia.com portal Splunk Alert: Alerta errores emision online Business Impact -: No, there is no overall degradation in payments on platform. And, there is no overall degradation in payments on platform. Action taken: We are proceeding to close this incident as we already have a an ongoing incident to check for the cause. Problem Ticket Required (y/n) : Not required, as this is a proactive check. Prevent Measures : Not required, as we have alert configured for same.

incident description: [OPTIMA] - Cannot book Critical for 9109 General Cargo commodity
resolution description: [Issue]:Cannot book Critical for 9109 General Cargo commodity [Impact]:User will not able to perform booking on iagcargo.com [Analysis]: We have raised with optima supplier and revived the below update from them. We have checked the above booking and could see the both booking was rejected by BA80. Below is the reason why BA80 rejected the bookings. In the BA80 request for this booking which sent from Optima has below details in commodity. Actual request : <Commodity> <CodeAction/> <Code/> <DescAction>I</DescAction> <Desc/> </Commodity> The expected info is : <Commodity> <CodeAction/> <Code/> <DescAction>I</DescAction> <Desc>GENERAL CARGO</Desc> </Commodity> This is the reason BA80 rejected this bookings with the error "COMMODITY DESCRIPTION ERROR". Below is the details why Optima sent request like above: Please find the below snapshot from the request which received from IAGPORTAL (commodity details). Actual request : <AlternateRouteCriteria> <OrigApt>LHR</OrigApt> <DestApt>HKG</DestApt> <DepartureDateTime>2021-03-03 17:01</DepartureDateTime> <ArrivalDateTime>2021-03-07 17:01</ArrivalDateTime> </AlternateRouteCriteria> <ProductCode ACTION="I">F</ProductCode> <VaProductCode>PRIORITISE</VaProductCode> <CommodityCode ACTION="I"/> <CommodityDesc ACTION="I"/> The expected info is : <AlternateRouteCriteria> <OrigApt>LHR</OrigApt> <DestApt>HKG</DestApt> <DepartureDateTime>2021-03-03 00:00</DepartureDateTime> <ArrivalDateTime>2021-03-07 00:00</ArrivalDateTime> </AlternateRouteCriteria> <ProductCode ACTION="">F</ProductCode> <VaProductCode>PRIORITISE</VaProductCode> <CommodityCode ACTION="">9109</CommodityCode> <CommodityDesc ACTION="">GENERAL CARGO</CommodityDesc> Due to this both the booking got rejected.     [Step Taken to Resolve]: Sent an email to user as below We have already made some changes in the code just to ensure and understand how the code is working on the basis of booking Type. (hopefully the change will work).   We have already raised the non-live environment request to the Environment team.(Pending with them for allocation)   We will keep you posted about the progress   Please Note : We have closed this incident and have raised the problem ticket (PBI000000087353) to cover same for future work.   [Problem Ticket Required? (Yes, No).]:No [Can this incident be prevented? (Yes, No)]:No

3.24-[OPTIMA]-AFLS have compared the booking accepted and rejected requests. In the rejected request , the flight departure time tag was missed due to which the booking got rejected with airport connection time. Please find the below details for your reference. Rejected Request: <Segment status="N"> <FlightSegmentId> <CarrierCode>IB</CarrierCode> <FlightNumber>3193</FlightNumber> <OrigApt>MUC</OrigApt> <DestApt>MAD</DestApt> <DepartureDate>2021-03-09</DepartureDate> <FlightDepartureDate>2021-03-09</FlightDepartureDate> </FlightSegmentId> <AllocationProductCode>PERFORM</AllocationProductCode> <TotalWeight>37.6</TotalWeight> <TotalVolume>0.404976</TotalVolume> <TotalPieceCount>5</TotalPieceCount> <SegmentProrationFactor>0.0</SegmentProrationFactor> </Segment> Accepted Request: <Segment status="N"> <FlightSegmentId> <CarrierCode>IB</CarrierCode> <FlightNumber>3193</FlightNumber> <OrigApt>MUC</OrigApt> <DestApt>MAD</DestApt> <DepartureDate>2021-03-09</DepartureDate> <FlightDepartureDate>2021-03-09</FlightDepartureDate> <ArrivalDate>2021-03-09</ArrivalDate> <AircraftType>31A</AircraftType> <DepartureTime>19:55</DepartureTime> <ArrivalTime GMTOffsetMinutes="60">22:45</ArrivalTime> </FlightSegmentId> <AllocationProductCode>M</AllocationProductCode> <AWBPriority>997000</AWBPriority> <TotalWeight>37.6</TotalWeight> <TotalVolume>0.404976</TotalVolume> <TotalPieceCount>5</TotalPieceCount> <SegmentProrationFactor>0.0</SegmentProrationFactor> </Segment> Due to the above reason, the IAGCAPI booking request got rejected. Attached are both accepted and rejected request and response for your reference. 3.22-[OPTIMA]-Have asked AFLSknow why Optima returned this error when trying to book via API and worked correctly when the booking was made later via Ebooking. 3.22-[OPTIMA]-AFLS updated that the request failed because of "AirportConnTime:Clearance Time at MAD is 90 mins" error 3.17-[OPTIMA]-We need to know why Optima returned this error when trying to book via API and worked correctly when the booking was made later via Ebooking. Pending with AFLS to advise. 3.16-[OPTIMA]-INC20256407 has been raised at AFLS's end.

incident description: ALERTA-CRI:Iberia.com portal Splunk Alert: Alerta errores emision online
resolution description: Issue Description: ALERTA-CRI:Iberia.com portal Splunk Alert: Alerta errores emision online Business Impact: no impact in this case, however online emisions could be impacted Analysis: We are getting this alert very frequently since few days now. As per our analysis, since March 3rd 21 the traffic on Amadeus is very low. It seems that certain traffic has been moved to NetPlus from Amadeus because from the same moment of time there is an upgradation in NetPlus Payments. And, there is no overall degradation in payments on platform(please find the attachment) This alert triggers from Splunk for the emissions happens via Amadeus, so because of degradation in traffic on Amadeus, the EOL transactions are also decreasing. Action taken: no action has been taken here. we will review the alert as per the current situation and if required we will take necessary actions Problem Ticket: not required, no more alerts occurred since then Preventive Measures: alerts have already set up for this

resolution description: ISSUE: AIP has not received MDM files for 15th March. IMPACT: These files are required by AIP.AIP will not be able to generate the reports for analysis and these reports are used by business. Analysis: We have checked ftpicc005mdm_live and ftpicc003mdm_live user on exchange node (172.21.232.199/ibftplinint.ib), the files were not available. We checked with MDM team and they informed us that the files were generated late, as the MDM batch took more time. Steps Taken to Resolve: We have checked ftpicc005mdm_live and ftpicc003mdm_live user on exchange node (172.21.232.199/ibftplinint.ib). Files were not available on exchange node, We checked with MDM team and they informed us that the files were generated late, as the MDM batch took more time. After the file generation we informed AIP and AIP confirmed that the files were received successfully. Problem Ticket Required? (Yes, No).: No , as the issue is related to source and target data. Can this incident be prevented? (Yes, No): No , as the issue is related to source and target data

incident description: [ICC002] SALESFORCE SERVICE CLOUD - I AM UNABLE TO ACCESS ANY GESTOR DOCUMENTAL IN ANY EXPEDIENTE
resolution description: Issue: Issue in accessing Gestor Documental section. Impact: User not able to close customer claims which directly impacts Iberia customer service. Analysis: Browser settings issue due to update. Steps Taken to Resolve: We shared below steps with user: To fix this issue for Gestor Documental you have to follow the below steps and follow the screenshots: 1. Open new tab in Google chrome (Control + T) 2. Enter “chrome://flags/” in URL and hit enter key 3. In Search box enter “SameSite by default cookies” 4. Set the “SameSite by default cookies” setting from “Default” to “Disabled”. B. Choose Disabled 5. In final step, relaunch the Google Chrome Browser. Problem Ticket Required? (Yes, No): No, the application is working as per designed. Can this incident be prevented? (Yes, No): No, the functionality was working as expected issue related to browser.

incident description: PROBLEMA referente a Facturación de Salida.
resolution description: Issue: Consulta sobre farebasis en Facturación Salida impact: Bajo Root Causes: Se ha revisado este tema, procedemos a explicar la casuística. El farebasis dentro de facturación de salida, se recupera de distintas fuentes. En primer lugar, se informa con la fuente de carga original (F50/IET), a la vez que se carga el cupón, informándose en la DVA. A continuación, hay en 3 valoraciones dónde se accede y actualiza el farebasis cuando hay información: -IET's -CRS's -Pseudoventa En este caso, el farebasis que muestras, se recupera así de la tabla TREPREH para la información de pseudoventa, en concreto se recupera del campo REHFBE, que es el farebasis elaborado, no el bruto. Si miramos los datos de la tabla, en el bruto sí estaría el valor RC: REHDOCR REHCUPR REHBIR REHCUR REHTDO REHLIN REHFVU REHORI REHDES REHTRA REHFBA REHFBE ----------- ------- ----------- ------ ------ ------ -------- ------ ------ ------ --------------- ----------- 2304026719 1 2304026719 1 TKT 0584 27/12/20 MAD SPC IB SDNNM2RC SDNNM2 2304026719 2 2304026719 2 TKT 3845 11/01/21 SPC MAD I2 LWNNM2RC LWNNM2RC El farebasis elaborado proviene de la salida de la rutina D22RN03, que para este caso concreto ha encontrado el código simple SD en el diccionario de radicales simples TIPBNCT. Para el cupón 02 no se elimina el radical RC al no haberse encontrado ningún código simple en los diccionarios. Si esperabais que para estos casos el farebasis tuviera el radical RC incluido, entendemos que se debería modificar ese diccionario, lo podéis hacer a través del siguiente online: https://web.corp.iberia.es/Estr_Tarifaria/ Si necesitáis usuario para poder acceder podéis realizar una petición. Steps taken: Se informa al cliente.
departamento cliente: RESP. CTROL ING Y GEST. A (3KEMI0)

incident description: MIFE: Valoración SPA sc 01 cia UX
resolution description: Issue: Consulta sobre valoración spa en mife Impact. Bajo Root causes: En el caso del billete 2393505618, inicialmente sí encuentra acuerdo SPA, pero es que al ser un sólo un cupón al final se tiene que quedar con el total del importe recuperado de la venta, que son 50,68 EUR en este caso, ya que no hay otro cupón que pueda absorber el residual. También se ha revisado algún caso con más de un cupón (billete 2393555717), y lo que les ocurre a estos es que ambos cupones encuentran acuerdo SPA inicialmente, pero el residual de diferencia entre el sumatorio del importe del acuerdo con el importe total del billete no se puede absorber por ninguno de los dos cupones, pues en la rutina de reparto ese importe se asigna a cupones operados por la compañía emisora (075 en este caso), y los dos cupones según el proceso se han operado por UX. Por tanto, los procesos revaloran y no aplican los importes SPA cómo tales, aunque se hayan encontrado los acuerdos. Steps taken Se informa a cliente.
departamento cliente: RESP. FACT. INTERL Y AG D (3KEMV0)

Issue: Consulta sobre cupones B&B en SJB Impact. Medio Root Causes: Con el cupón de 2020 (075-2393097071-02) hemos podido ver de dónde vienen estos casos. A los procesos del R35 del SJB, además de entrar la información del contable de ingresos, también entra información proveniente de la tabla TIPCIDC que se carga con el fichero de IDEC. De esta tabla se recogen todos aquellos cupones cuya compañía exista con valor S en el campo SJBLIQ del diccionario TDICSJB (JL, BA y AY según el mismo). También se comprueba que el source code sea 00, 01 o blancos. En este caso es 01. Para los casos anteriores ya no existen ficheros intermedios ni datos en la tabla TIPCIDC, pero comprobando la NBDP para los que están cuadra esta explicación, todos los revisados tienen utilización de factura de entrada, y en lo que muestras en el correo anterior la transportista también está en las compañías con el campo SJBLIQ a S. Steps taken: Se informa a cliente.

incident description: ESC005: Space issue in E drive in GaudiPr1.
resolution description: Issue: ESC005: Space issue in E drive in GaudiPr1. Analysis: We have analyzed the issue and found that there are some temp file which is taking more spaces. And, there is no overall degradation in payments on platform. Action taken: We are proceeding to close this incident as we already have a an ongoing incident to check for the cause. Issue: We took remote and checked that unable to play the videos that were inserted in the PPTs in Power point 2016 desktop(version 1902). The same videos can be played in the web application. This is the first time users are trying to insert the online videos in this kind. Justification to use online vidoes: User says that to download and nsert the videos, the size of videos may vary upto 1GB. Also upto 20 videos they need to insert in a presentations. These PPTs are created for the Flight and cabin crew training purposes. So it is required to add the online videos. Testing and results: And when we try to insert the online video, with YouTube or with Weblink, it will not search in the internet and show any results. Attached the screenshots for the same. It seems that the PPT is not connecting to internet to load the data. We checked in some of the test machines, it is the same. User also checked in all the 13 machines listed. It is the same issue. We checked in different versions of O365 like, 1808, 1902(which user has), we upgraded to 2008 for testing purpose and checked. The issue remains the same in all versions and in all the machines. Same is working fine in user´s personal PC. Can add and play the videos. We have checked the PPT settings and also checked registry settings. It is all seems to be fine. All the users have E3 license and all the machines have O365 installed. With all these tests, the issue is that the PPT is not connecting to internet to load the data. This must be checked with the network team or the security team. Assigned the ticket INC000001505468 to SSI for the same issue. Hence cancelling the ticket.

Hemos contactado con Maria José Nieto, y ha podido consultar los billetes en el acceso de BSPLink. Los billetes fueron enviados desde TKT pero están rechazados por los siguientes motivo que ella ha analizado: 0752100893737 - este voy a corregir la moneda, lo reemitio el Call Center en EUR cuando debio de reemitir en COP. 2100900285 -> va junto con este EMD que tambien fallo 0759020033543. El Call Center hizo reemision en PNR nuevo (el PNR original estaria caducado) y le puso un OSI POSI con una IATA erronea. Lo corrijo con la IATA de la agencia. 2100894023 --> fue reemitido por NDC con una tasa adicional de 0.35, pero en la FOP no se ha cobrado nada. En realidad es una reemision sin cobro adicional, pero al haber una tasa a pagar, hay discrepancia entre las tasas y la FOP. Los dos primeros se van a modificar y volver a enviar pero el último no se pueden modificar sin distorsionar los datos y que luego esto provoque errores en futuros reembolsos. Los tres son errores funcionales ajenos a nuestra aplicación.

resolution description: Issue Description: ALERTA-CRI:Iberia.com portal Splunk Alert: Alerta errores emision online Business Impact: no impact in this case, however online emisions could be impacted Analysis: We are getting this alert very frequently since few days now. Action taken: no action has been taken here as not required. platform iks fine Problem Ticket: not required, no more alerts occurred since then Preventive Measures: alerts have already set up for this

Issue: We had recieved this morning the following message from MainframeReporting@iberia.es: "Warning: Carga de ficheros TTL" Analysis: We have analyzed the issue and found that we have not received the load_date.txt and sip_data.txt file yesterday we have received only tpm_data.txt file. In load_date.txt it is showing date as 210323 which should be 210324 to load the data into database. Business Impact: Business will not able to see the data in case of job failure. Resolution: Below Steps need to be follow: 1. Connected to MainframeReporting@iberia.es to send the updated load_date.txt file 2. Once file received wait for the wait for the TTL_DAILY_LOAD job to trigger 3. Check in the table CFG_LOAD_LOG if data has been loaded successfully or not CAN THIS ISSUE BE PREVENTED?: No. The File was delayed from the source Team and therefore, no issue with the application. PROBLEM TICKET REQUIRED?: No. As the files are received from the source Team. There was delay in sending the files due to which the load Plan failed.

resolution description: ISSUE: AIP has reported that the dumbo_subscribe_card field marked as 61 is not reported for few customers. Impact : If AIP will not receive this data correctly ,they will not be able to generate the reports at their end required for business. Analysis : We have checked with ATOS for the reason for the discrepancy reported by customer and they have informed us that there is no issue, as per system design the subscribe and unsubscribe data of Santander One Iberia Plus program appears as 61 in the files  only on day when customer register’s or unsubscribe the program. Steps Taken to Resolve: 1.We have checked with ATOS for the reason for the discrepancy reported by customer. 2. As per our source team, the subscribe and unsubscribe data of Santander One Iberia Plus program appears as 61 in the files  only on day when customer register’s or unsubscribe the program. There is no such discrepancy as this the criteria which is used by source team for fetching information for all Santander Clients. 3. we contacted AIP team and asked them if the information is sufficient . AIP confirmed that we can close this incident. Problem Ticket Required? (Yes, No).: No , as the issue is related to source and target data. Can this incident be prevented? (Yes, No): No , as the issue is related to source and target data.

incident description: [PDF007]Datalake system haven’t received few IBPLUS files for today 27th Mar-21
resolution description: ISSUE: AIP has reported that they have not received IBPLUS file for 27th March. impact : If AIP will not receive this data ,they will not be able to generate the reports at their end required for business. Analysis : We have checked the path on exchange node where these files are sent by source at user ftpicc003ibplliveon exchange node and the file IB Plus were not available and we also checked the s3 bucket to make sure if the files were archived. Steps Taken to Resolve: 1.We have checked the path on exchange node where these files are sent by source at user ftpicc003ibpllive on exchange node and the files were not available. We followed-up with ATOS team for the reason for missing file. 2. We checked the server and files was there at ATOS external server. 3. Files were received late on 27th March, we asked ATOS to provide us the reason for delay in file transfer and ATOS updates us that the files were delay due to large amount of data present in the which took more time to upload. We again checked at the destination location for the IBPLUS files. And the files were present at the location /ibftplinint/live/ftpicc003loyalive/ . 4. we contacted AIP team to check and verify if the files are available. AIP confirmed that the files are received . Problem Ticket Required? (Yes, No).: No , as the issue is related to source and target data. Can this incident be prevented? (Yes, No): No , as the issue is related to source and target data.

incident description: Proactively observed there is ESC005 - KO degradation of service on the platform.
resolution description: Issue: ESC005 - KO degradation of service on the platform. Analysis: We have analyzed the issue and found that reports are not refreshing in GaudiPr4 platform because server is not accessible/ Services was hanged.. There is a degradation of service on the Hyperion platform in gaudipr4. Business Impact: Business were not able to access the reports, This caused delay in staff duties. Resolution: Below steps has been processed to solve this issue: 1. Restart the events. 2. Restarted the GaudiPr4 platform services. CAN THIS ISSUE BE PREVENTED?: No. this is not a recurring issue. PROBLEM TICKET REQUIRED?: No. as the issue is temporary.

incident description: ALERTA-CRI:Iberia.com portal Splunk Alert: Alerta errores emision online NO AVISAR ON-CALL Necesidad
resolution description: Issue Description :ALERTA-CRI:Iberia.com portal Splunk Alert: Alerta errores emision online Business Impact -: No, there is no overall degradation in payments on platform. Analysis : We can see a decrease in transactions for old web platform for which there is alreay an ongoing incident "INC000001498517 - Degradation detected at Amadeus payment gateway since 3/03/2021 15:00" It seems that certain traffic has been moved to NetPlus from Amadeus because from the same moment of time there is an upgradation in NetPlus Payments. And, there is no overall degradation in payments on platform. Action taken: We are proceeding to close this incident as we already have a an ongoing incident to check for the cause. Problem Ticket Required (y/n) : Not required, as this is a proactive check. Prevent Measures : Not required, as we have alert configured for same.

incident description: [SABRE FPM]no les actualiza la red de vientos
resolution description: • Impacto: error en vientos al calcular plan en FPM. • Acciones: Sabre nos comenta que varios proveedores llevan dando error unos días. Reinician servicios GRIB. Despacho prueba y el cálculo acaba ok y sin errores. • Prueba: detalle en “detalle de trabajos”

[SSI]: Buenas tardes, Con respecto a su incidencia, el equipo de soporte ha indicado lo siguiente: "Hablamos con el usuario y hacemos varias pruebas de visualización con la aplicación de GAUDI RealTime. Nos dice el usuario que las tareas se ven pequeñas, pero vemos que no se trata del mismo error que se producía en el pasado. Se trata de un problema de resolución de pantalla en los equipos que maneja el usuario, no es un problema en la aplicación. Es necesario que acuda un técnico de EUC para que haga pruebas de resolución de pantalla del usuario para ver si las tareas se ven algo mas grandes." Hemos asignado la incidencia al equipo de EUC, que es el encargado de soporte local sin embargo al usted tener un computador externo a Iberia, no se le puede dar soporte. Por lo que le recomendamos que contacte directamente con un técnico de su soporte local que pueda asistirle y ayudarle a verificar la resolución de la pantalla para que pueda ver las tareas en un tamaño adecuado. Por ende, procedemos a cerrar la incidencia. En caso de tener alguna duda o inquietud con respecto al ticket, por favor dejadlo saber. Muchas gracias, Un cordial saludo. Quedamos a la espera de su respuesta. No responda a este mensaje ya que se trata de una respuesta automática del sistema. Contacte nuevamente con nosotros por teléfono al 915874700 o por email al ssi@iberia.es aportando el nº de referencia de su incidencia. Muchas gracias, Un cordial saludo.

Una vez se ejecute, se relanzará el proceso fallado y finaliza ok.
